            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/textView18"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="1. Preheat the Oven:

Preheat your oven to 425°F (220°C).
2. Prepare the Carrots:

Peel the carrots and trim the ends.

If the carrots are thick, cut them in half lengthwise for even roasting.

3. Make the Caramelized Roasting Sauce:

In a bowl, whisk together olive oil, honey or maple syrup, balsamic vinegar, Dijon mustard, salt, and black pepper.
4. Toss the Carrots:

Place the carrots in a large bowl.

Pour the caramelized roasting sauce over the carrots and toss until they are well-coated.

5. Roast the Carrots:

Spread the carrots in a single layer on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.

Roast in the preheated oven for 20-25 minutes or until the carrots are tender and caramelized, tossing them once or twice during the cooking time.

6. Garnish and Serve:

Remove the roasted carrots from the oven.

Transfer them to a serving dish and drizzle any remaining sauce from the baking sheet over the top.

Garnish with fresh parsley or thyme if desired.

7. Serve:

Serve the caramelized roasted carrots as a side dish with your favorite main course.

Enjoy the sweet and savory flavors of these delicious caramelized carrots!"
